				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The NES doesn't have that many memory mapped registers, so I think using either addresses or names is OK. The Atari 2600, on the other hand, has nearly 70 memory mapped registers (most are in ZP, but even that doesn't really make them any easier to remember!), so there's no way anyone can memorize all that. Ever since I first worked with the 2600, a adopted the habit of naming registers on the NES too, and I think that does result in slightly more readable code.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

